                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1412" type="surname" value="JAMES"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1412" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE JAMES</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Henry-street, White-horse-lane, Stepney. On the morning of the 9th of April, at half-past ten o'clock, I was in Stepney fair, looking at Clarke's show—the prisoner came by, and took up a bundle—his blouse was buttoned up—he put it under his left arm, and walked away—I told the prosecutrix, and then the policeman—he took the prisoner, who had got 100 yards.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> You said at the office yon saw me pick it up half-a-yard from the stall? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> The stall had just been moved, and the bundle was put under the table.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">COURT</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Where did he put it? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Under his coat—I found it there.</p>
